gemini-1.5-pro.ocr_text:
GREAT SMOKY MOUNTAINS NATIONAL PARK
GSMNP10729

Plants of Tennessee

Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt

Tennessee: Sevier County
35.64269° Latitude  -83.50105° Longitude  2990 ft. Elevation
Quadrangle: Gatlinburg                       West Prong Little Pigeon Watershed
T. 11S, R. 72E, Sect. 10

The Great Smoky Mountains National Park. Just south of the U.S. Route 441 where it bends strongly across from the Chimneys Campground. North side of the West Prong of the Little Pigeon River southwest of the south tip of the bend in US 441. Coordinate Datum: WGS84/NAD83.

Growing in woods under shrub dominated area (*Kalmia latifolia*) with scattered *Acer rubrum*, *Magnolia fraseri*, *Oxydendrum arboreum*, *Pinus rigida*, *Quercus prinus*, *Sassafras albidum*, *Rhododendron maximum*, *Salix rotundifolia*, etc. Evergreen perennial herb growing in numerous clumps here.

42265 Loy R. Phillippe & James R. Payne
7 October 2009

Illinois Natural History Survey (ILLS)

SERNEC Digitization Project - Tennessee Herbarium Consortium


*Galax urceolata*
